This paper deals with information diffusion over social networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of social and information sciences. Specifically, the paper focuses on learning models for information diffusion that incorporate asynchronous time delay, which involves statistical modeling and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper also deals with behavioral data analysis, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
